Full credit must go to auditor-general Tsakani Maluleke for telling it like it is, and not mincing her words when she reprimanded underperforming municipalities for lack of accountability at local government level. In a first, Maluleke’s office referred six municipalities to the Financial Intelligence Centre to investigate their unexplained accounting practices when handling public finances. Some municipalities even  failed to provide their auditors with their books – meaning their books are in a shambles. Take them on, Tsakani. Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here.